@ENDNODE

@NODE SB "How can you reach me ?"
@SMARTWRAP
@{b}Author@{ub}@{LINE}

This is the third public release of the rewritten SimpleFind3 so there can be a lot of bugs in it!
If you find some bugs (even in this guide) or have suggestions to improve
SimpleFind3, you should contact me.


You should also contact me if you want to create a new language catalogue for
SimpleFind3.  I will then send you the files required for writing a catalog (via
E-Mail only).  Currently there are the following language catalogues with
exception of English and German):

@{CODE}
  Norwegian  by Eirik Bogsnes and Robert Taje
  Spanish    by Ignacio Garcia Cuadrad
  Swedish    by Fredrik Ismyren
  Croatian   by Ivan Kosak
  Dutch      by Johan Banis
  French     by Didier Giron

@{BODY}

The German guide was created by JŘrgen Urbanek, the Spanish one by
Ignacio Garcia Cuadrad and the Dutch version by Johan Banis.


Very great thanks goes to the authors.


Very many thanks also go to all the people who have supported SimpleFind and who
have helped me make the version better than their predecessors, by sending suggestions,
bug reports and solutions. I hope I get the same feedback for SimpleFind3, too.


If you have designed some new SimpleFind3 icons I would be pleased if you could
send them to me. They will then be included in the next release of SimpleFind3.
The icons in the distribution archive are copyright by there creators.


Also feel free to send me harddisks, gfxcards, disks, CDs or
money ;-)

@{CODE}

Address:
   Sebastian Bauer
